From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: cppmega.mlx <noreply@example.com>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 13:10:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] tilelang: add E8M0 block-scaled layout primitive

Add a first-class DSL layout object for MXFP8/E8M0 block scales:

  T.BlockScaledLayout(
      scale_dtype="e8m0",
      axis="contracted_k",
      block_size=32,
      layout="logical_unswizzled_k_axis_blocks",
  )

and expose T.e8m0_to_float(byte) with the Metal-compatible E8M0 semantics used
by Apple MXFP8: byte 0 and byte 0xFF are sentinels that decode to zero, while
all other bytes decode as 2 ** (byte - 127).

The layout plugs into T.fp8_scaled_matmul through the existing scale metadata:

  T.fp8_scaled_matmul(
      A_fp8,
      A_scale,
      B_fp8,
      B_scale,
      C,
      transpose_B=True,
      block_scale_layout=T.BlockScaledLayout.e8m0_k32(),
  )

Lowering metadata remains explicit:

  scale_format="e8m0_block_k32"
  scale_block_size=32
  scale_axis="contracted_k"

For the Sparse-MLA Path C shape this preserves the concrete scale contract:

  A_scale shape: (K / 32,)
  B_scale shape: (N, K / 32) or broadcast (K / 32,)
  scale block:   kb = k // 32

